00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:36,770
and the difference in particular

295
00:09:36,770 --> 00:09:39,600
between active and passive transformations.

296
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,860
You can think either way,

297
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:44,280
active or passive,

298
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,440
either way.

299
00:09:46,140 --> 00:09:49,660
There's an appropriate argument that gives the...

300
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:49,760
I don't know if you can see it,

301
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:50,040
but there's an appropriate argument

302
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:50,320
that gives the same result.

303
00:09:50,980 --> 00:09:52,800
But let me just spell it out for you.

304
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:58,080
Let's think about it the following way.

305
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:00,120
We have a particle on a line as an example,

306
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,040
just as an example.

307
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:04,960
And now somebody comes along and says,

308
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,520
perform.

309
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:09,200
That's something you're required to do.

310
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,420
Perform the transformation,

311
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:13,940
x goes to x plus 1.

312
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:16,540
What exactly does that mean?

313
00:10:16,740 --> 00:10:16,980
Oh,

314
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:17,800
incidentally,

315
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:18,770
we imagine that the line is going

316
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:19,740
to be the same as the line.

317
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:20,040
It is a coordinate.

318
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,100
So that every point on it is labeled.

319
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,200
Every point has a name.

320
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:30,720
This one is named x equals...

321
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,000
Well,

322
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,800
this one's called named x equals minus 1.

323
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,140
This one's named x equals 0 and so forth.

324
00:10:35,220 --> 00:10:36,790
Think of the coordinate labels as

325
00:10:36,790 --> 00:10:38,360
just the names of the points,

326
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:38,840
if you like.

327
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:39,940
Alright,

328
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,400
but of course it's done in a special way,

329
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,560
not arbitrary.

330
00:10:43,860 --> 00:10:46,300
What does it mean to say perform

331
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,740
the transformation x goes to x plus 1?

332
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:50,400
It could mean two things.

333
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:54,600
It could mean relabel the points so that every point

334
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:58,400
that was originally labeled x is now labeled x plus 1.

335
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:02,080
This one was originally labeled x equals 0.

336
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:05,300
And after the relabeling it becomes,

337
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,180
let's call it x prime equals 1.

338
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:11,300
Particle stays in exactly the same position.

339
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:14,300
If it happened that there was a potential energy,

340
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:15,140
for example,

341
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:16,060
that looked like this,

342
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,870
the potential energy would not

343
00:11:17,870 --> 00:11:19,540
change because the particle hasn't moved.

344
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:19,720
Right?

345
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:21,180
Okay.

346
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:25,870
The other definition of what you could mean by perform

347
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:30,420
this transformation is take the particle from where it is.

348
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:33,520
Keep the coordinates fixed but move it.

349
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:35,540
Wherever it is,

350
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:36,600
whatever x it's at,

351
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,560
move it to x plus 1.

352
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,080
Under that transformation,

353
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,880
the potential energy does change.

354
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:49,040
The first notion is called a passive transformation.

355
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,940
You don't move anything.

356
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:52,460
You just relabel points.

357
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:57,520
The second version is called an active transformation.

358
00:11:57,780 --> 00:12:00,700
You literally take everything in the system,

359
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:03,260
not just one particle but every particle

360
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:05,820
and whatever else you have besides particles,

361
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,410
and lift them and move

362
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:08,860
them one unit to the right.

363
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:11,000
That's an active transformation.

364
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,120
It's quite clear that the active transformation,

365
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,560
since it moves the particle,

366
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:18,480
will change the potential energy.

367
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:19,320
Yeah?

368
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:19,860
So,

369
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:22,960
then whatever is causing this potential energy to

370
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:26,060
exist is not considered part of the system?

371
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:26,260
Right.

372
00:12:26,820 --> 00:12:27,300
Right.

373
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,040
Exactly.

374
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:28,980
Exactly.

375
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,340
We're going to come back to that.

376
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,600
That's exactly right,

377
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,580
so let me state it now.

378
00:12:36,620 --> 00:12:39,480
In saying that the system was a particle,

379
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:44,300
we of course are first of all making an approximation,

380
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,920
but more than that,

381
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:48,460
we're dividing it.

382
00:12:48,460 --> 00:12:51,340
We're dividing the entire system into two parts.

383
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,200
One part is the particle,

384
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,440
the other part is the Earth with

385
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,680
all its hills and valleys and so forth.

386
00:12:58,560 --> 00:12:59,140
Okay.

387
00:13:01,380 --> 00:13:02,460
If I,

388
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:03,020
of course,

389
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:04,440
were to move everything,

390
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,020
including the Earth,

391
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:08,400
the potential energy would not change.

392
00:13:10,180 --> 00:13:13,170
But what we're focusing on is the particle thinking

393
00:13:13,170 --> 00:13:16,160
of the Earth as just too heavy to respond.

394
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:22,360
It's a situation where with essentially no loss of accuracy,

395
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:25,940
we can say the Earth just doesn't move.

396
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:27,560
Of course,

397
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:29,240
there's a slight loss of accuracy there.

398
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,560
If the particle accelerates or decelerates,

399
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,520
it recoils against the Earth,

400
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,580
the Earth moves a little bit.

401
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:37,480
But because the Earth is so heavy,

402
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,260
it's irrelevant.

403
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,500
Or it's for practical purposes,

404
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,440
we can ignore the motion of the Earth

405
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,380
and we just say the Earth is fixed.

406
00:13:46,719 --> 00:13:48,679
It gives rise to a potential

407
00:13:48,679 --> 00:13:50,640
which is a definite function of x.

408
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:53,100
And we're going to leave it that way.

409
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:55,680
We're not going to change the location of the Earth.

410
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,560
We're not going to change the

411
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:59,160
location of the top of the potential,

412
00:13:59,160 --> 00:13:59,840
for example.

413
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,960
And we're just going to say the transformation we're going to

414
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:05,760
do is to move everything relative to the Earth in effect.

415
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:07,260
Okay.

416
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:07,940
So,

417
00:14:07,940 --> 00:14:10,350
but we simplify it by just saying there's

418
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:12,760
a potential energy which is a function of x.

419
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,640
And therefore,

420
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:15,920
if we move the particle,

421
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:16,140
we move the potential.

422
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,360
The potential energy changes.

423
00:14:18,540 --> 00:14:18,980
Okay.

424
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:21,400
So that's the notion of an active transformation.

425
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:25,080
And I think it's easiest to think about,

426
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:25,380
yeah,

427
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:26,360
the active version.

428
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:28,880
So one thing that still confuses me,

429
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:29,720
even with this description,

430
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:32,220
when we did the rotation last time,

431
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:34,700
so we not only changed the positions,

