00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:56,580
And when we rotated all the positions,

451
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:58,960
we also rotated the velocity.

452
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:01,600
Okay.

453
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:04,000
So we not only rotated,

454
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,640
we not only rotated the

455
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,280
position at an instant of time,

456
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:07,720
I should say,

457
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:07,920
okay,

458
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:08,660
one more thing.

459
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,340
When we say do the transformation

460
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:11,880
x goes to x plus 1,

461
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:14,460
we mean that every time,

462
00:15:16,439 --> 00:15:17,400
all times,

463
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,520
send x to x plus 1.

464
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:23,310
When we say to rotate the coordinate

465
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:26,740
system so that x varies a little bit,

466
00:15:26,740 --> 00:15:28,120
we mean at all times.

467
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:29,480
We'll come to it in a minute.

468
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:32,080
I'm going to go back through

469
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,300
it just to refresh you very quickly.

470
00:15:34,820 --> 00:15:35,200
All right.

471
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,440
So here's the game.

472
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:40,160
We have some configuration space,

473
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:42,180
which is the space of the q's.

474
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:43,440
The q's,

475
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,680
incidentally,

476
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:45,820
I will use x.

477
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:49,080
When thinking about Cartesian coordinates for particles.

478
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:50,480
Otherwise,

479
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,420
more generally,

480
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:52,820
we'll discuss q's.

481
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:54,840
But x's are just a special case.

482
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:57,380
All right.

483
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,400
So we have our q space.

484
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:00,740
Here's our q space.

485
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,760
The system,

486
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:04,500
and it's multidimensional,

487
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,100
or it's not multidimensional.

488
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,480
It's got some number of dimensions.

489
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:10,660
And a configuration is just a point in that space.

490
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:11,560
Now,

491
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:12,420
there are many configurations.

492
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:13,940
All right.

493
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,800
For every point in this space.

494
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:16,720
There's a configuration.

495
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:22,280
And now what we mean by a coordinate transformation,

496
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,640
an active coordinate transformation now,

497
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,860
is that we take the system,

498
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:28,260
wherever it happens to be,

499
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:30,420
and move it to a new position.

500
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,700
We move it to a new position.

501
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:35,260
If this point is called q sub i,

502
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:40,860
then we shift q sub i by an amount.

503
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,600
Let's call it delta q sub i.

504
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,800
It's a shift of q sub i by an amount.

505
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:48,580
This is delta q.

506
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:50,640
All right.

507
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:52,640
Which may,

508
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:53,420
in fact,

509
00:16:53,420 --> 00:16:55,720
depend on where we are.

510
00:16:56,340 --> 00:16:57,280
In other words,

511
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:59,020
the delta q over here might be

512
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:00,760
different than the delta q over here.

513
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,440
Might be different than the delta q over here.

514
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:05,839
But it's fixed.

515
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:07,200
It's fixed once and for all,

516
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,380
meaning to say that there's a definite transformation.

517
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:13,119
But the transformation,

518
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:14,520
the amount that you shift,

519
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,800
may depend on where you are.

520
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,900
That's allowed.

521
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:18,180
Okay.

522
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:19,669
So then delta q sub i

523
00:17:19,669 --> 00:17:21,079
is not just a constant then.

524
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:23,420
It depends on where you are.

525
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:24,720
And in order to indicate that,

526
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:27,940
we introduce a function for each i,

527
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:30,840
which is a function of all the coordinates,

528
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,640
and a small constant delta.

529
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:39,480
Now the small constant delta is just really for bookkeeping.

530
00:17:39,820 --> 00:17:41,560
It's kind of a redundant notation.

531
00:17:41,860 --> 00:17:42,820
If we just thought that f,

532
00:17:42,820 --> 00:17:44,800
we could imagine that f was just small.

533
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,320
But it's a sort of redundant notation.

534
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:49,980
We'll think of f as not necessarily being small,

535
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:52,340
but make the shift small by

536
00:17:52,340 --> 00:17:54,700
having a sort of universal constant,

537
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,860
which is assumed to be small,

538
00:17:56,860 --> 00:18:01,400
so that delta squared can be ignored and so forth.

539
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:02,920
All right.

540
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:05,110
This is the nature

541
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:07,300
of an infinitesimal coordinate transformation.

542
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:09,240
Every point moves.

543
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:12,100
And the points,

544
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,560
the coordinates of the points,

545
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,780
may move.

546
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,030
But they don't move by an

547
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:17,260
amount which depends on where you are.

548
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,200
That's this over here.

549
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:20,960
All right.

550
00:18:20,980 --> 00:18:24,180
That's an infinitesimal coordinate transformation.

551
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:27,990
And that's what we mean when

552
00:18:27,990 --> 00:18:31,740
we speak of an infinitesimal coordinate transformation.

553
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:34,900
Now,

554
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:35,900
when you do so,

555
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:39,200
the potential energy may change.

556
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:41,400
Of course the potential energy may change.

557
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,740
This is an active transformation.

558
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:47,680
It may even be that the kinetic energy transforms.

559
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:48,260
Okay.

560
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:50,120
Let's say what happens to velocities.

561
00:18:50,780 --> 00:18:51,300
Oh,

562
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:53,770
the one thing that we do assume is

563
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:56,240
that these f sub i's are independent of time.

564
00:18:57,180 --> 00:18:58,600
When we shift things,

565
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:01,900
we shift them by amounts which don't depend on time.

566
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:04,220
Okay.

567
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,280
For example,

568
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:09,860
if we're just talking about a shift of x,

569
00:19:09,860 --> 00:19:12,440
x goes to x plus a small amount,

570
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:16,020
that small amount is assumed not to depend on time.

571
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,260
And therefore,

572
00:19:17,260 --> 00:19:18,320
in that case,

573
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:22,340
the velocity itself does not shift.

574
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:25,770
The velocity doesn't shift if we made the

575
00:19:25,770 --> 00:19:28,560
transformation x goes to x plus a constant.

576
00:19:29,620 --> 00:19:30,180
Then,

577
00:19:30,180 --> 00:19:32,300
if we time differentiate this,

578
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:34,720
it says that x dot goes to

579
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:37,140
x dot with no change in the velocity.

580
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:38,120
Okay.

581
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:39,180
Why?

582
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:42,140
Because we moved everything to the right by one unit.

583
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:45,050
Moved it both at time t and also at

584
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:47,660
time t plus a little t plus a bit.

585
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:51,040
And so the velocity hasn't changed in between.

586
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:52,880
Okay.

587
00:19:53,140 --> 00:19:54,000
In general,

588
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,320
there may be a change in the velocity,

589
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,800
but for this particular case,

590
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,240
there would be no change in the velocity.

591
00:19:58,320 --> 00:19:58,500
Yeah?

592
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,870
Is that final delta there in

593
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:02,840
your equation a constant across all points?

594
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,300
This delta is a constant.

595
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:04,740
Yeah.

596
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:08,520
This delta is a fixed constant which in the

597
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,380
end of the day we'll say is very small.

598
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:12,540
Okay.

599
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,130
And it's just a bookkeeping device so

600
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:17,260
that we don't have to call this small.

601
00:20:17,380 --> 00:20:17,720
That's all.

602
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:19,540
We'll see why in a moment

603
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:20,700
we don't want to call that small.

604
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:25,660
It's a bookkeeping device to say all the transformations

605
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:30,000
are small and of the same order of magnitude.

606
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:31,140
Good.

607
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:34,340
Some of these f's may be zero.

608
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,420
For example,

609
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:37,920
if we're talking about two-dimensional space,

610
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:38,700
x and y,

611
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:42,260
we make a transformation only of the x coordinate.

612
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:43,950
x goes to x plus a

613
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:45,640
little bit with no change in y.

614
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:49,820
Then the y component of f would be zero.

615
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,200
The x component would not be.

616
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:53,000
Okay.

617
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:53,680
So as I said,

618
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:56,020
we keep track of the smallness by the constant delta.

619
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,320
All right.

620
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,120
As I said,

621
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,980
when you do such a transformation,

622
00:21:02,980 --> 00:21:06,040
the potential energy will in general change.

623
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,400
It may not,

624
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,600
but it may.

625
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:10,540
It may change.

626
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:11,480
In addition,

627
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,240
even the case of a small energy,

628
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:12,240
it may change.

629
00:21:12,260 --> 00:21:13,540
Even kinetic energy may change.

630
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,300
For example,

631
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:18,000
the kinetic energy in some coordinates,

632
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:21,720
in some non-Cartesian coordinates,

633
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:27,900
might have the form of t of q.

634
00:21:28,850 --> 00:21:29,780
That's just a function.

635
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:33,140
Any function of q times q dot squared.

636
00:21:35,340 --> 00:21:36,600
Some function.

637
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:39,240
An example would be polar coordinates

638
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:42,680
in which the theta term,

639
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:44,980
the term associated with the theta velocity,

640
00:21:44,980 --> 00:21:46,500
involves r.

641
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:47,800
Remember that?

642
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:48,760
r theta dot squared?

643
00:21:49,140 --> 00:21:49,700
Right.

644
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:52,240
So you can have kinetic energies,

645
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:54,040
which also have dependence on q.

646
00:21:54,260 --> 00:21:55,600
And then when you move things,

647
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:57,200
even the kinetic energy might

648
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,800
vary if you make a transformation.

649
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:00,180
So in general,

650
00:22:00,180 --> 00:22:04,240
the entire Lagrangian may vary,

651
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:07,020
and usually will.

652
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:11,480
The situation where the Lagrangian doesn't change,

653
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,660
and moreover,

654
00:22:13,660 --> 00:22:16,240
doesn't change no matter where you are,

655
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:17,920
not only at the point

656
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,600
where the system happens to be.

657
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:21,520
You might say,

658
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:21,840
all right,

659
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,960
I'm interested in the system being right over here,

660
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,430
and then I do a

661
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:26,900
transformation which takes it over here,

662
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:29,030
and find out that it doesn't

663
00:22:29,030 --> 00:22:31,160
change the Lagrangian at this point.

664
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:32,320
No,

665
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:32,360
no.

666
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:34,000
That's not enough to say there's a symmetry.

667
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:35,680
To say there's a symmetry means

668
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,000
that at every point in time,

669
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:37,000
there's a symmetry.

670
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:37,020
At every point,

671
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:38,320
no matter where you are,

672
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:40,480
the Lagrangian doesn't change.

673
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:42,660
For example,

674
00:22:42,660 --> 00:22:43,620
for a potential energy,

675
00:22:43,620 --> 00:22:44,710
let's just think about what it

676
00:22:44,710 --> 00:22:45,800
would say about a potential energy.

677
00:22:46,820 --> 00:22:49,100
The potential energy is a function of x and y.

678
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:54,480
And the coordinate transformation I may be

679
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:57,100
interested in is just an x shift.

680
00:22:57,720 --> 00:22:59,680
Let's take the case of just an x shift,

681
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,080
so that x shifts a little bit.

682
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:04,390
What does it mean to say that the potential

683
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:06,880
energy doesn't change if you make an x shift?

684
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,840
It means it doesn't depend on x.

685
00:23:10,740 --> 00:23:12,180
No matter where you are,

686
00:23:12,180 --> 00:23:14,000
up or down,

687
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,480
left or right,

688
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:19,860
if the potential energy doesn't change when you vary x,

689
00:23:19,860 --> 00:23:21,300
what does it mean about v?

690
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:23,480
It means it's independent of x,

691
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,580
but it can depend on y.

692
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:27,160
It can depend on y because

693
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,680
y doesn't change when you shift x.

694
00:23:29,540 --> 00:23:30,580
On the other hand,

695
00:23:30,580 --> 00:23:34,920
if I were to say a different type of transformation,

696
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,980
shifting vertically,

697
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:39,960
and saying the potential energy doesn't change,

698
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,700
would say v was a function of x.

699
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:46,060
And if you were to say even stronger that the

700
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:49,920
potential doesn't change no matter which direction you translate in,

701
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:51,820
it would say the potential were a constant.

702
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,320
The potential was a constant,

703
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:55,720
completely independent of x and y.

704
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:57,360
Okay,

705
00:23:57,360 --> 00:24:01,370
so that's the notion of the potential energy changing

706
00:24:01,370 --> 00:24:05,380
or not changing when you make a small transformation.

707
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:06,980
But in particular,

708
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:09,530
we mean when we say that the

709
00:24:09,530 --> 00:24:12,080
potential doesn't change under a small transformation.

710
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:13,960
It doesn't change wherever you are,

711
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,000
under that transformation.

712
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:19,380
If both the potential and the kinetic,

713
00:24:19,380 --> 00:24:21,480
or let's say more generally,

714
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,750
if the Lagrangian itself does not

715
00:24:23,750 --> 00:24:26,020
change when you make a transformation,

716
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:29,000
then that is a symmetry.

717
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,180
Wherever you are,

718
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:32,420
you make such a little motion,

719
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:34,000
at all times,

720
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,040
at all times,

721
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,180
then the Lagrangian,

722
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:39,240
if the Lagrangian doesn't change,

723
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,960
then it's a symmetry.

724
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:43,280
Yeah?

725
00:24:44,580 --> 00:24:47,120
So the Lagrangian has to stay the same,

726
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:48,200
but does that...

727
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:48,620
Same value,

728
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:50,640
same numerical value no matter where you start.

729
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:53,340
But does that condition have to be true

730
00:24:53,340 --> 00:24:55,520
separately for the potential energy and for the kinetic?

731
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:55,840
No.

732
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:57,040
In many cases,

733
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,400
in many cases the Lagrangian doesn't even divide

734
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:01,760
up into a kinetic and a potential energy neatly.

735
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,980
So that's a good question.

736
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,200
And the answer is no.

737
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:07,200
It does not have to be separate.

738
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:10,700
It's kind of hard.

739
00:25:10,780 --> 00:25:12,660
It would be kind of hard if one

740
00:25:12,660 --> 00:25:14,540
term didn't depend on velocity and the other didn't,

741
00:25:14,540 --> 00:25:15,560
did and didn't.

742
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:17,200
But in general,

743
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,660
the most general Lagrangians won't divide up

744
00:25:19,660 --> 00:25:22,120
in a neat way into kinetic and potential.

745
00:25:22,620 --> 00:25:24,460
They'll just be functions of q and q dot.

746
00:25:25,420 --> 00:25:27,080
And then it wouldn't even be possible

747
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:28,740
to even ask the question in that case.

748
00:25:28,940 --> 00:25:30,020
So the answer is no.

749
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:33,380
Only the whole Lagrangian has to not change.

750
00:25:33,500 --> 00:25:33,600
Yeah?

751
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,780
I'm probably reading it too much,

752
00:25:35,780 --> 00:25:38,290
but are you saying that it won't change or that

753
00:25:38,290 --> 00:25:40,800
it will change so little we can ignore the change?

754
00:25:41,180 --> 00:25:41,500
Okay.

755
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,100
This is an infinitesimal transformation.

756
00:25:46,780 --> 00:25:49,920
The most we could expect if we made

757
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:53,060
such a transformation would be an infinitesimal change.

758
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:55,720
If we make an infinitesimal shift,

759
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,650
the most we can expect is

760
00:25:57,650 --> 00:25:59,580
an infinitesimal change in the Lagrangian.

761
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:03,980
To say that there is no change means no function.

762
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:04,740
There is no first order change.

763
00:26:04,860 --> 00:26:08,100
No change proportional to the delta itself.

764
00:26:08,740 --> 00:26:09,420
Now,

765
00:26:09,420 --> 00:26:12,330
that's enough to prove that

766
00:26:12,330 --> 00:26:15,240
a finite version of the transformation,

767
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:23,560
which just means doing it repeatedly enough times,

768
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:25,730
usually means a number of times

769
00:26:25,730 --> 00:26:27,900
proportional to one over the small number,

770
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:30,700
doing the transformation over and over

771
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,640
until you build up a finite transformation,

772
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:35,020
that also doesn't change the Lagrangian.

773
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:38,340
If it's the case that it doesn't

774
00:26:38,340 --> 00:26:41,440
change the Lagrangian no matter where you are.

775
00:26:41,620 --> 00:26:44,770
A simple example would be a potential

776
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:47,920
which you might think depends on x.

777
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:48,380
Okay?

778
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,660
You might think it depends on x.

779
00:26:50,260 --> 00:26:51,140
And then you say,

780
00:26:51,140 --> 00:26:51,460
all right,

781
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:53,420
what happens if I move x a little bit?

782
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:55,760
Then there's a variation of x,

783
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:56,440
a little bit,

784
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,220
the change,

785
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:57,560
sorry,

786
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:59,120
the variation of the potential,

787
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:01,480
the small change in the potential,

788
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:04,130
is just the derivative of v

789
00:27:04,130 --> 00:27:06,780
with respect to x times delta x.

790
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:10,900
Now,

791
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:13,170
supposing it's true that this is equal

792
00:27:13,170 --> 00:27:15,440
to zero no matter where you start.

793
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,960
And delta x is just a number.

794
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:21,320
Delta x is just delta,

795
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:22,220
the number,

796
00:27:22,220 --> 00:27:22,820
the small number.

797
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:27,300
Suppose it's true that no matter where you are,

798
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:30,280
the small shift doesn't change v.

799
00:27:32,340 --> 00:27:35,240
Then that says dv dx is equal to zero.

800
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:38,020
And not only does it say dv dx is

801
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:40,220
equal to zero at the point where the particle is,

802
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:43,100
it's zero no matter where the particle could be.

803
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:46,060
If this is equal to zero for all x,

804
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:48,220
then dv dx is equal to zero.

805
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,240
And that,

806
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:49,680
of course,

807
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:52,040
does say that v is constant.

808
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:54,960
And it also means that if you were to

809
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:57,760
build up a finite shift by little infinitesimal ones,

810
00:27:58,040 --> 00:27:59,700
it still wouldn't change v.

811
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:01,600
So typically,

812
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:06,710
if you have a situation where the small change

813
00:28:06,710 --> 00:28:11,820
in coordinates does not lead to a comparable change,

814
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,100
in other words,

815
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:16,100
a first order change in the Lagrangian,

816
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:17,620
then that's a symmetry.

817
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:22,300
And you only mean,

818
00:28:22,300 --> 00:28:23,320
you only have to check,

819
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:29,680
you only have to check that the Lagrangian hasn't changed.

820
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:31,400
It hasn't changed to lowest order,

821
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:33,360
meaning to order delta.

822
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:34,920
Delta squared,

823
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:35,960
you don't worry about.

824
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,420
You don't have to worry about it,

825
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:42,220
because long as it's flat for all x,

826
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:44,360
or more generally,

827
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:45,480
as long as it's,

828
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:45,960
so to speak,

829
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:47,500
flat for all q,

830
00:28:49,100 --> 00:28:51,580
then repeating the transformation endless numbers of

831
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:54,060
times won't change the value of the function.

832
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:55,580
Okay,

833
00:28:55,580 --> 00:28:59,320
so that's the notion of a symmetry.

834
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:01,940
And when you have a symmetry,

835
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:03,200
you have a conserved quantity.

836
00:29:03,380 --> 00:29:05,340
So I won't go through the derivation again.

837
00:29:05,740 --> 00:29:07,260
We'll just write down what it is.

838
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:11,520
If this is your little shift,

839
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:14,380
then the conserved quantity,

840
00:29:14,380 --> 00:29:16,000
which I called q last time,

841
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:16,920
q for quantity,

842
00:29:19,340 --> 00:29:20,180
q is,

843
00:29:20,180 --> 00:29:23,880
notice that each coordinate is being shifted.

844
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:25,800
Some of them may not be shifted,

845
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:28,620
but that just means some of these are zero.

846
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:31,000
The general situation is every

847
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,300
one of the coordinates gets shifted,

848
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:35,190
then q is the sum of all the coordinates

849
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,860
of a contribution from each one of the coordinates,

850
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:44,040
and the sum is multiply the momentum conjugate to

851
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:49,000
q sub i by the little shift f sub i.

852
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:54,160
Now you can see why one doesn't want to

853
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:56,560
think of f sub i as an infinitely small quantity.

854
00:29:57,020 --> 00:29:58,580
I want to think of this as a,

855
00:29:58,580 --> 00:29:59,240
you know,

856
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:01,200
as a finite quantity.

857
00:30:01,420 --> 00:30:03,210
So I don't want to

858
00:30:03,210 --> 00:30:05,000
necessarily restrict f to be small.

859
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:08,290
Then it follows that the time

860
00:30:08,290 --> 00:30:10,420
derivative of this is equal to zero.

861
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:12,640
That's the theorem we proved last time.

862
00:30:13,860 --> 00:30:16,300
And you can go back over the derivation of it,

863
